# Recruitment project ↔ candidates

## Relation row

- Table: `u_yf_projekty_rekrutacyjne_relations_members_entity` (`crmid` = project, `relcrmid` = candidate).
- Handler: `GetRelatedMembers` — use **`createMembership($projectId, $candidateId, $status)`** for inserts.
- Do **not** change `create(int, int): bool` signature on the parent `GetRelatedList` (PHP fatal). Parent `create()` must stay 2-arg; throw or delegate if called without status.

## Initial status contract

| Source | `recruitment_status_rel` |
|--------|--------------------------|
| CV / `CandidateApplicationSideEffects::bindCandidateToProject` | `PPL_APPLIED` via `createLink(..., STATUS_APPLIED)` |
| Manual (kanban +, related-list Select, `RelationAjax`) | `PPL_MANUALLY_ADDED` via `save_related_module` → `createMembership` |

`cvs_applied_number` counts only `PPL_APPLIED`. New status must be added to `RelationTrigger::getRecruitmentStatusOptions()` and `RecruitmentStatusTransition::SUGGESTED_DEFAULTS`.

## Kanban widget (summary tab)

- Load project via `ProjektyRekrutacyjne\Models\Record::getInstanceById()` — `getRelatedCandidates()` is module-specific (not on `Base\Models\Record`); add `/** @var \App\Modules\ProjektyRekrutacyjne\Models\Record $project */` for Intelephense. Same pattern as `CandidatesRecruitmentProjects` widget.
- Rendered server-side in `SummaryViewWidgets.tpl` (`RecruitmentProjectKanban.tpl`) — **not** a `widgetContainer_*` AJAX widget.
- **Layout (4 tables):** (1) `PPL_MANUALLY_ADDED` alone — „Dobre kandydatury” + (+); (2) screening — 3 cols @ 33% (`.recruitment-kanban-screening`); (3–4) interview + rejections — 4 cols @ 25% each (`.recruitment-kanban-quarters`). Wrapper: `.recruitment-project-kanban`.
- **Styles:** `public/modules/ProjektyRekrutacyjne/resources/RecruitmentProjectKanban.css` — loaded in `Views/Detail.php` → `getHeaderCss()`; minify after edit. No inline `<style>` in tpl.
- **`loadWidgets()` does not refresh the kanban.** After manual add, update chips in the DOM (`Detail.js` → `refreshUiAfterManualCandidatesAdd`) or return candidate payloads from `AddManualCandidatesAjax`.
- (+) button: `KanbanSearchCandidatesModal` (skills, `;`-separated) → `Candidates` popup filtered by `cv_text` (`CvSkillsSearch`, param `cv_skills`) → `AddManualCandidatesAjax` + multi-select. Class `.js-kanban-add-manual-candidate` — white circle, gray `+`, **portal-orange** (`#EC971F`) on hover/focus; styled in `RecruitmentProjectKanban.css` (no `btn-success`).

## Manual-add UX (do not regress)

- No success toast on add (chips appearing is enough).
- All candidates already linked: info skip message only — **not** `PLL_NO_SUCH_RECORD`. API: `success` true when `added` or `skipped` non-empty; JS must not treat skip-only as failure.

## Side effects

- `relateEntities(..., 'getRelatedMembers')` → `EntityAfterLink` → `NewCandidateInProject` (comments differ for applied vs manual).
- Import uses `createLink()` directly (not `relateEntities`) to keep `PPL_APPLIED` and still run the same handler.

## Candidates module rename (metadata gotchas)

- **RecruitmentApplication related tab** on Candidates Detail: needs `vtiger_fieldmodulerel.relmodule = 'Candidates'` on `candidate_id` (field 303290). Stale `Kandydaci` → HTTP 500 in `RelationListView::getCreateViewUrl()`.
- **Picklist fields** (`status`, `availability`, `work_time_type`): table must match field name (`vtiger_candidate_status`, etc.) — see `m260609_000006`.
- **Verification**: `bin/check_candidates_migration.php` after migrations; migrations `m260609_000001`–`000007` in `migrations/Users/`.

## Kanban status change + transition mail

- Manual drag: `Detail.js` → `ChangeCandidateStatusManuallyAjax` → `GetRelatedMembers::changeStatus()` (whitelist: `RecruitmentStatusTransition`).
- Transition mail matrix: `RecruitmentStatusTransitionMail::resolveMailActions()` splits by `delivery_mode` — **`auto`** → `sendAutoTemplates()` + JSON `autoSend` toast; **`prompt`** → JSON `mailPrompt.templateIds` → `Vtiger_Index_Js.triggerSendEmailModal` (`Candidates`, `sourceModule`/`sourceRecord` = project). See `recruitment-settings.mdc`.
- Screening Accept/Reject and workflows do **not** use the mail matrix.

## Candidate files (CV, consents, etc.)

- **Canonical storage:** Documents module + `vtiger_senotesrel` — Candidate detail → Więcej → **Documents** (`getAttachments`, `m260613_000006`). ADD/SELECT + per-row **CV** (Set as CV) via `RelatedListLeftSideExtras`.
- **Preview only:** Summary widget **`CandidatesPreview`** (`CandidatesPreview.tpl`) reads **`cv_img_file`** (uitype **330**, JSON array in `u_yf_candidates`). **No widget title in template** — image only (`.summaryWidgetContainer--cv-preview`). Empty if no Set-as-CV / transform yet, even when Documents exist. First summary column (`m260616_000002`; DB widget label is config-only). Header thumbnail: `DetailViewHeaderTitle.tpl` via `Record::getCVPathname()`.
- **Image URL:** `/file.php?module=Candidates&action=MultiAttachment&field=cv_img_file&record={id}&key={key}` — handler `Candidates/Files/MultiAttachment.php`. Requires login (session cookie); unauthenticated → 401 blank `<img>`.
- **UiType 330:** `MultiAttachmentJson` — `getDBValue()` JSON-encodes arrays; `isAjaxEditable()` false (SaveAjax inline edit once wrote literal `"Array"` into DB).
- **Template pitfalls:** never `height="100%"` on preview `<img>` without a fixed-height parent (Firefox collapses to 0px). Do not Smarty `escape:'url'` on `file.php` URLs (over-encodes). Use explicit `max-width:100%; height:auto` (`.candidates-cv-preview__image`).
- **CV import:** `DocumentHelper::saveAndDeleteFile` links new Document to **Candidates** only (`prepareRelationsString('Candidates', …)`).
- **Counts:** `u_yf_candidatescf.documents_count` via `RefreshDocsNumber` on link/unlink.
- **Export CV ZIP** (`Candidates/Actions/ExportCvZip.php`, mass action on **Candidates list** and project→Candidates related list) must follow **`cv_img_file`** (the one Set-as-CV doc), **not** filter Documents by `title='cv'`. Export the **original Document blob** (pdf/docx), not the `cv_img_file` JPEG preview. Resolve source doc: `sourceDocumentId` in JSON (new) → `fetchDocumentRowById(notesid)` → legacy `name` prefix `{id}_{hash}` — **`id` is often storage file id** (basename of `storage_path`, legacy `transformFileToCV`), not `notesid`; then `fetchCandidateDocumentByStorageFileId` matches linked doc by `notesid` or `storage_path` suffix `/{id}`. Fallback: `cv_img_file` blob + `ensureZipEntryExtension` (`.jpg` from mime). Zip entry name uses document `original_name` (keeps `.pdf`/`.docx`). JS: related list → `ProjektyRekrutacyjne_RelatedList_Js.triggerExportCvZip` + `collectRelatedCandidateIds()`; Candidates list → `ListView.js` `triggerExportCvZip` — see `listview-javascript-playbook.mdc` for `selected_ids` encoding.

## Related-list Excel export (Eksport do Excel)

- Project→Candidates related list uses **`QuickExport::ExportRelatedToExcel`** (not the cvid-based `ExportToExcel`). Triggered by `ProjektyRekrutacyjne_RelatedList_Js.triggerQuickExportToExcel()` (`public/modules/ProjektyRekrutacyjne/resources/RelatedList.js`), which posts `parentModule`, `record`, `relatedModule`, `tab_label`, `mode=ExportRelatedToExcel`, `selected_ids`.
- Server rebuilds the **same `RelationListView`** as the view: columns from `getHeaders()` (incl. `recruitment_status_rel`), rows via new `RelationListView::getEntriesByIds($ids)` (filters `id` on the relation query, keeps Screening tab condition). Cell render mirrors `RelatedListContents.tpl` 3-rule logic — name/uitype-4 → `getDisplayValue`, `fromOutsideList` → `Field::getDisplayValue` (translated picklist label for status), else `getListViewDisplayValue`.
- The old cvid path (`ExportToExcel`) crashed with empty `viewname` (`getCustomViewFromFile('')` → „Nie znaleziono widoku”) because this related list has **no cvid dropdown** (`CUSTOM_VIEW_LIST = []`).

## ListPreview empty state (do not regress)

- `ProjektyRekrutacyjne/RelatedList.tpl` ListPreview branch: the `empty($RELATED_RECORDS)` case **must still `{include RelatedListContents.tpl}`** so column headers + per-column search survive filtering to zero (else user loses filters and can't clear them). Matches Base related-list behavior: **no „Lista jest pusta” message** — just an empty `tbody`. Empty wrapper uses `.c-list-preview--empty` (`float:none; width:100%`).
- Narrow checkbox/action columns: tightened in `RelatedList.css` (`.listViewEntriesTable` first two cols → `width:1px; white-space:nowrap`) because ListPreview table is `min-width:max-content`, so `width="4%"` on `<th>` is ignored.

## Job advertisement links field (`job_advertisement_links`, uitype 300)

- HTML generated server-side in `Handlers/Calculations.php` → `generateJobAdvertisementLinks()` on **`EntityBeforeSave`** (one link per `vtiger_application_source.generate_link=1`). Handler must be registered in `vtiger_eventhandlers` (migration `m260630_000006`) **and** in `EventHandler::$classNameMap` — see `architecture.mdc`. Type hint is `\App\Events\EventHandler` (not `\App\EventHandler` → fatal TypeError when it fires).
- **uitype 300 content is run through `Purifier::purifyHtml()`** on display → inline `onclick` / `<button>` are stripped. Copy UI must use allowed tags only (`<a>`/`<span>`/`<div>` + `class`); the URL lives in `<a href>` and JS reads it. Don't rely on `title` (also stripped).
- Render = **orange pills** (`.job-ad-link-copy`), styled by `public/modules/ProjektyRekrutacyjne/resources/JobAdvertisementLinks.css` (loaded in `Views/Detail.php` → `getHeaderCss()`; minify after edit). Click → copy via `Detail.js` `registerJobAdvertisementLinkCopy()` + purple `.is-copied` flash + `JS_NOTIFY_COPY_TEXT` toast. JS keeps a `tr td:nth-child(3)` fallback for legacy table-format rows not yet re-saved.
